==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Soothsay
<hw>Sooth"say`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sooth</ets> + <ets>say</ets>; properly to say truth, tell the
truth.]</ety> <def>To foretell; to predict.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧You can not
<xex>soothsay</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Old
<xex>soothsaying</xex> Glaucus' spell.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soothsay</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Soothsay
<hw>Sooth"say`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A true saying; a
proverb; a prophecy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Omen; portent. Having</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God turn the same to good <qex>soothsay</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soothsayer</ent>⟦br⟧
